1
00:01:33,093 --> 00:01:33,560
We're worried she

2
00:01:33,560 --> 00:01:34,594
may not last more than a few days.

3
00:01:35,295 --> 00:01:36,229
She has signed the consent form.

4
00:01:36,296 --> 00:01:37,163
The donor registration is in place too.

5
00:01:37,664 --> 00:01:38,665
I'm counting on you, Dr. Guo.

6
00:01:39,265 --> 00:01:40,166
I understand, Director Zhou.

7
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:41,334
As soon as a donor becomes available,

8
00:01:41,401 --> 00:01:42,168
we'll notify your center

9
00:01:42,168 --> 00:01:43,002
right away.

10
00:01:43,236 --> 00:01:44,204
Okay. Thank you.

11
00:01:55,081 --> 00:01:56,282
So that means,

12
00:01:56,783 --> 00:01:58,318
if I don't go on ECMO,

13
00:01:59,118 --> 00:02:00,653
I won't make it.

14
00:02:01,588 --> 00:02:02,388
But

15
00:02:03,823 --> 00:02:05,091
if I do go on ECMO,

16
00:02:05,525 --> 00:02:06,960
there may not be any improvement either.

17
00:02:07,894 --> 00:02:08,495
Maybe

18
00:02:08,995 --> 00:02:10,396
before a donor even comes,

19
00:02:11,764 --> 00:02:12,565
I'll already be gone.

20
00:02:13,566 --> 00:02:15,635
We need to understand the worst-case scenario,

21
00:02:16,536 --> 00:02:17,770
but still hold on to hope.

22
00:02:19,405 --> 00:02:20,373
How long

23
00:02:21,407 --> 00:02:22,609
would I need to be on ECMO

24
00:02:24,010 --> 00:02:27,080
before we know whether it's helping?

25
00:02:27,413 --> 00:02:28,414
Ideally,

26
00:02:28,448 --> 00:02:29,282
we should see improvement

27
00:02:29,315 --> 00:02:30,450
in about a week.

28
00:02:30,917 --> 00:02:32,152
If it really works,

29
00:02:32,485 --> 00:02:34,687
we'll know clearly within two weeks.

30
00:02:36,156 --> 00:02:36,623
Okay.

31
00:02:39,792 --> 00:02:41,161
Then two weeks it is.

32
00:02:44,597 --> 00:02:45,164
Linlang.

33
00:02:46,132 --> 00:02:47,934
Let's agree on this beforehand.

34
00:02:48,668 --> 00:02:50,203
If it's more than two weeks

35
00:02:52,171 --> 00:02:53,773
and there's still no improvement,

36
00:02:55,375 --> 00:02:56,376
then we stop.

37
00:03:11,124 --> 00:03:12,725
We can't let it become endless.

38
00:03:16,729 --> 00:03:17,430
Two weeks

39
00:03:17,463 --> 00:03:18,932
isn't an absolute standard.

40
00:03:20,833 --> 00:03:21,601
I know.

41
00:03:23,636 --> 00:03:24,837
This is the time

42
00:03:26,072 --> 00:03:27,373
I'm giving myself.

43
00:03:28,374 --> 00:03:31,311
If I do everything I can

44
00:03:32,679 --> 00:03:34,280
and still can't

45
00:03:35,014 --> 00:03:36,249
keep Linlang's mother with her,

46
00:03:39,185 --> 00:03:40,453
then I can't really

47
00:03:42,255 --> 00:03:43,690
leave her with nothing at all.

48
00:03:53,666 --> 00:03:55,168
How did it come to this?

49
00:03:56,069 --> 00:03:57,503
It shouldn't be like this.

50
00:03:59,239 --> 00:04:00,206
Why?

51
00:04:01,307 --> 00:04:01,975
Linlang.

52
00:04:03,142 --> 00:04:04,410
Let's not cry.

53
00:04:05,345 --> 00:04:06,312
The two of us

54
00:04:07,046 --> 00:04:08,615
agreed on this already.

55
00:04:09,749 --> 00:04:10,550
If

56
00:04:11,985 --> 00:04:14,887
Mom's surgery doesn't go well,

57
00:04:15,989 --> 00:04:18,524
just think of me as going far away

58
00:04:18,825 --> 00:04:19,759
on a trip.

59
00:04:21,394 --> 00:04:23,162
Everyone has this day eventually.

60
00:04:24,530 --> 00:04:26,266
When you miss Mom,

61
00:04:28,234 --> 00:04:29,769
touch your belly button.

62
00:04:34,040 --> 00:04:35,441
This is where you and Mom

63
00:04:36,409 --> 00:04:38,311
were once connected.

64
00:05:05,705 --> 00:05:06,906
I told you she needed close monitoring.

65
00:05:06,973 --> 00:05:07,707
You couldn't be careless.

66
00:05:08,307 --> 00:05:09,676
How did the infection get this bad?

67
00:05:11,344 --> 00:05:12,645
Can your postoperative ICU team

68
00:05:12,912 --> 00:05:14,147
show a little more responsibility?

69
00:05:16,649 --> 00:05:17,750
Even though she's on ECMO,

70
00:05:18,317 --> 00:05:19,552
with her current condition,

71
00:05:19,752 --> 00:05:21,120
we don't know if she can recover.

72
00:05:22,488 --> 00:05:23,523
Even if she does recover,

73
00:05:24,490 --> 00:05:25,591
she probably still won't be able

74
00:05:25,625 --> 00:05:26,292
to undergo the transplant.

75
00:05:26,759 --> 00:05:27,293
It's fate.

76
00:05:28,494 --> 00:05:29,128
I don't agree.

77
00:05:30,963 --> 00:05:32,265
If the infection can be corrected,

78
00:05:32,832 --> 00:05:33,933
then it isn't

79
00:05:33,966 --> 00:05:34,634
an absolute contraindication for transplant.

80
00:05:36,402 --> 00:05:37,370
If you can't do it, Director,

81
00:05:38,171 --> 00:05:38,705
I can.

82
00:05:55,722 --> 00:05:56,889
Never admit defeat until the very end.

83
00:05:57,724 --> 00:05:59,125
A doctor can't give up before the patient does.

84
00:06:07,233 --> 00:06:07,767
What are you doing?

85
00:06:09,435 --> 00:06:10,470
This is a talisman I got for her.

86
00:06:10,503 --> 00:06:11,237
It's to protect her.

87
00:06:11,604 --> 00:06:13,039
I hope she gets better soon.

88
00:06:47,273 --> 00:06:47,874
Director Sheng.

89
00:06:50,610 --> 00:06:51,210
Who are you?

90
00:06:51,911 --> 00:06:52,612
A patient's family member?

91
00:06:53,513 --> 00:06:54,747
You don't recognize me?

92
00:06:55,047 --> 00:06:56,549
I'm You Xiaoli's daughter.

93
00:06:56,916 --> 00:06:57,517
Director Sheng,

94
00:06:57,750 --> 00:06:58,584
after my mom's surgery,

95
00:06:58,584 --> 00:06:59,952
why has she become so seriously ill?

96
00:07:00,987 --> 00:07:02,922
That can't be explained in a few words.

97
00:07:03,122 --> 00:07:04,957
We'll talk in detail during rounds.

98
00:07:05,291 --> 00:07:06,092
I have a meeting soon.

99
00:07:06,092 --> 00:07:06,692
I'm busy right now.

100
00:07:07,326 --> 00:07:08,361
Director Sheng, please wait.

101
00:07:08,528 --> 00:07:09,028
Director Sheng.

102
00:07:10,396 --> 00:07:10,997
You said one year

103
00:07:11,030 --> 00:07:12,064
would absolutely be no problem.

104
00:07:12,265 --> 00:07:13,599
Why aren't you keeping your word?

105
00:07:16,402 --> 00:07:17,003
Director Sheng.

106
00:07:17,370 --> 00:07:18,371
At the time you said

107
00:07:18,571 --> 00:07:19,872
that living to a hundred couldn't be guaranteed,

108
00:07:20,239 --> 00:07:20,907
but one year

109
00:07:20,973 --> 00:07:22,175
would absolutely be no problem.

110
00:07:22,642 --> 00:07:24,143
But now my mother's condition

111
00:07:24,143 --> 00:07:25,044
is getting worse and worse.

112
00:07:26,078 --> 00:07:26,913
Surgery

113
00:07:27,613 --> 00:07:29,048
always carries risks.

114
00:07:30,116 --> 00:07:31,651
You signed the surgical informed consent form

115
00:07:31,951 --> 00:07:33,052
beforehand too.

116
00:07:33,386 --> 00:07:34,720
But you said yourself

117
00:07:34,921 --> 00:07:35,655
that after surgery,

118
00:07:35,721 --> 00:07:37,223
my mom could live a normal life.

119
00:07:37,490 --> 00:07:38,157
She could,

120
00:07:38,591 --> 00:07:39,625
but that wasn't a guarantee.

121
00:07:40,393 --> 00:07:40,993
I think

122
00:07:41,360 --> 00:07:42,528
you misunderstood me.

123
00:07:42,728 --> 00:07:44,230
But you said

124
00:07:44,397 --> 00:07:46,132
one year would absolutely be no problem.

125
00:07:46,199 --> 00:07:46,833
How could I possibly

126
00:07:46,866 --> 00:07:48,167
make such a boast?

127
00:07:51,671 --> 00:07:52,038
But...

128
00:07:52,638 --> 00:07:53,973
But you did say it.

129
00:07:54,207 --> 00:07:55,675
Right in front of me and my mom.

130
00:07:56,409 --> 00:07:57,243
Right here.

131
00:07:57,677 --> 00:07:58,611
Everything depends on evidence.

132
00:07:59,445 --> 00:08:00,146
Do you have evidence?

133
00:08:00,947 --> 00:08:01,914
If you do, show it.

134
00:08:03,316 --> 00:08:04,650
How can you be like this?

135
00:08:05,084 --> 00:08:06,285
You're a department director.

136
00:08:06,385 --> 00:08:07,553
How can you lie to people?

137
00:08:07,587 --> 00:08:09,255
Why are you yelling at me here?

138
00:08:10,156 --> 00:08:11,023
People who don't know might think

139
00:08:11,090 --> 00:08:11,958
I did something to you.

140
00:08:12,225 --> 00:08:13,726
Doctors aren't gods.

141
00:08:14,093 --> 00:08:15,962
For such a complex surgery,

142
00:08:16,495 --> 00:08:17,797
there are bound to be many variables.

143
00:08:18,364 --> 00:08:19,198
But that isn't

144
00:08:19,232 --> 00:08:20,333
what you said at the time.

145
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:21,367
You said

146
00:08:21,601 --> 00:08:23,436
you were sure and confident about the surgery,

147
00:08:23,469 --> 00:08:24,570
so we agreed to it.

148
00:08:24,871 --> 00:08:26,005
We trusted you so much.

149
00:08:26,105 --> 00:08:27,373
How can you do this?

150
00:08:27,640 --> 00:08:29,876
It isn't necessarily true that your mother's prognosis

151
00:08:30,042 --> 00:08:31,277
will be bad.

152
00:08:31,677 --> 00:08:32,879
Treatment and recovery

153
00:08:33,246 --> 00:08:34,146
take time.

154
00:08:34,881 --> 00:08:35,748
Isn't she still

155
00:08:35,815 --> 00:08:36,282
in the general ICU

156
00:08:36,282 --> 00:08:36,749
right now?

157
00:08:37,316 --> 00:08:38,985
We're doing everything we can to save her.

158
00:08:39,352 --> 00:08:41,387
If you come after me now,

159
00:08:41,921 --> 00:08:42,855
how are the doctors supposed to feel?

160
00:08:43,356 --> 00:08:44,724
I can let it go,

161
00:08:44,957 --> 00:08:46,525
but the morale of the medical team

162
00:08:46,692 --> 00:08:48,160
will be badly affected.

163
00:08:49,362 --> 00:08:50,096
That would be very bad

164
00:08:50,129 --> 00:08:50,863
for your mother.

165
00:08:52,398 --> 00:08:53,366
You don't have to believe me.

166
00:08:53,799 --> 00:08:54,533
You can transfer her to another hospital.

167
00:08:54,934 --> 00:08:55,534
I won't stop you.

168
00:08:57,670 --> 00:08:58,204
Anything else?

169
00:08:59,972 --> 00:09:00,506
If not, leave.

170
00:09:17,156 --> 00:09:17,623
Linlang.

171
00:09:21,160 --> 00:09:21,794
What's wrong?

172
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:35,708
Director Sheng

173
00:09:37,009 --> 00:09:38,711
really promised us with such certainty.

174
00:09:39,745 --> 00:09:41,681
He said living to a hundred couldn't be guaranteed,

175
00:09:43,683 --> 00:09:44,784
but within one year,

176
00:09:44,784 --> 00:09:46,185
there would be no problem.

177
00:09:46,852 --> 00:09:47,553
That's why my mom and I

178
00:09:47,586 --> 00:09:49,255
agreed to the surgery.

179
00:09:52,158 --> 00:09:53,125
What else did he say?

180
00:09:54,093 --> 00:09:54,694
He said

181
00:09:55,361 --> 00:09:56,996
the surgical risk was very high.

182
00:09:58,798 --> 00:09:59,365
But...

183
00:09:59,765 --> 00:10:01,534
but in the few cases he had done,

184
00:10:01,567 --> 00:10:02,935
there had been no problems.

185
00:10:04,003 --> 00:10:05,204
After surgery, they all

186
00:10:05,237 --> 00:10:06,639
went back to normal lives.

187
00:10:08,574 --> 00:10:10,710
He said this was our chance.

188
00:10:11,811 --> 00:10:13,846
But now he won't admit it.

189
00:10:14,146 --> 00:10:16,349
How can someone be so cruel?

190
00:10:44,677 --> 00:10:45,444
Director Zhou.

191
00:10:46,312 --> 00:10:47,713
Can you still help me?

192
00:10:50,316 --> 00:10:50,683
I...

193
00:10:51,317 --> 00:10:52,885
We can hire a lawyer

194
00:10:53,486 --> 00:10:54,387
and find an adviser.

195
00:10:56,055 --> 00:10:57,089
I must seek justice

196
00:10:57,156 --> 00:10:58,190
for my mother.

197
00:11:00,993 --> 00:11:02,294
Her biggest wish now

198
00:11:02,595 --> 00:11:03,529
is that next year,

199
00:11:03,763 --> 00:11:05,364
she can walk onto the stage by herself,

200
00:11:05,564 --> 00:11:06,565
without anyone supporting her,

201
00:11:06,966 --> 00:11:08,267
to attend my coming-of-age ceremony.

202
00:11:08,868 --> 00:11:10,870
That is my promise to my daughter.

203
00:11:11,637 --> 00:11:12,805
She doesn't want me to have regrets.

204
00:11:13,072 --> 00:11:14,440
I don't want her to have regrets either.

205
00:11:14,807 --> 00:11:15,508
I hope

206
00:11:15,875 --> 00:11:17,043
she can live with dignity

207
00:11:18,411 --> 00:11:19,345
and with quality of life.

208
00:11:21,280 --> 00:11:22,014
Has Director Sheng come by?

209
00:11:22,515 --> 00:11:23,382
He handed her over after surgery

210
00:11:23,382 --> 00:11:24,350
and hasn't come again.

211
00:11:24,483 --> 00:11:25,584
He asked once over the phone

212
00:11:25,918 --> 00:11:27,153
and told us to monitor her closely.

213
00:11:27,253 --> 00:11:28,287
Would this model,

214
00:11:28,587 --> 00:11:29,989
smaller and lighter,

215
00:11:30,122 --> 00:11:30,990
be more suitable for him?

216
00:11:31,991 --> 00:11:32,558
Let's use this one.

217
00:11:33,159 --> 00:11:34,093
Dongli's first case,

218
00:11:34,226 --> 00:11:35,027
and the first case in China.

219
00:11:35,127 --> 00:11:36,162
Those two points alone

220
00:11:36,362 --> 00:11:37,763
are enough publicity.

221
00:11:38,130 --> 00:11:39,632
Some medical decisions

222
00:11:40,199 --> 00:11:40,800
are not made

223
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:42,001
solely for the patient.

224
00:12:12,131 --> 00:12:12,598
Come in.

225
00:12:14,667 --> 00:12:16,135
These are You Xiaoli's medical records,

226
00:12:16,402 --> 00:12:17,236
the operative notes,

227
00:12:17,636 --> 00:12:18,637
and the informed consent form.

228
00:12:22,274 --> 00:12:23,442
An aortic valve replacement was also performed

229
00:12:23,809 --> 00:12:25,878
during the operation.

230
00:12:26,278 --> 00:12:26,712
Yes.

231
00:12:27,646 --> 00:12:28,647
The indication

232
00:12:28,881 --> 00:12:30,049
is somewhat stretched.

233
00:12:33,052 --> 00:12:34,386
But the patient and her family

234
00:12:34,854 --> 00:12:35,855
also signed

235
00:12:36,255 --> 00:12:37,323
the informed consent form, didn't they?

236
00:12:38,424 --> 00:12:39,158
And

237
00:12:39,492 --> 00:12:41,427
the risks, benefits, and drawbacks were explained too.

238
00:12:41,994 --> 00:12:42,928
According to what the patient's daughter

239
00:12:43,028 --> 00:12:43,863
told me,

240
00:12:45,231 --> 00:12:45,931
Director Sheng's explanation

241
00:12:46,132 --> 00:12:47,566
to them at the time

242
00:12:48,067 --> 00:12:49,168
was clearly misleading.

243
00:12:49,769 --> 00:12:50,569
The hospital requires

244
00:12:51,103 --> 00:12:52,471
that for such high-risk surgeries,

245
00:12:52,705 --> 00:12:53,973
video

246
00:12:54,006 --> 00:12:54,840
and audio evidence be kept during the consent discussion.

247
00:12:55,441 --> 00:12:56,609
Director Sheng failed to do that too.

248
00:13:01,714 --> 00:13:02,114
Okay.

249
00:13:03,249 --> 00:13:03,849
Okay.

250
00:13:04,150 --> 00:13:05,484
I will talk to Sheng Nian about this.

251
00:13:06,352 --> 00:13:06,952
President Wang,

252
00:13:07,520 --> 00:13:08,287
at this point,

253
00:13:09,355 --> 00:13:09,989
talking to him

254
00:13:09,989 --> 00:13:10,890
won't mean anything anymore.

255
00:13:11,991 --> 00:13:12,958
He'll never admit it.

256
00:13:14,426 --> 00:13:15,327
Then what do you suggest?

257
00:13:15,694 --> 00:13:16,962
I think the patient's daughter's request

258
00:13:16,996 --> 00:13:17,596
is reasonable.

259
00:13:18,998 --> 00:13:19,999
The hospital should convene

260
00:13:19,999 --> 00:13:21,200
an evaluation and appraisal committee

261
00:13:21,734 --> 00:13:22,868
to investigate

262
00:13:23,369 --> 00:13:24,270
You Xiaoli's case.

263
00:13:25,604 --> 00:13:26,205
At the same time,

264
00:13:26,405 --> 00:13:27,773
from what I know of Director Sheng,

265
00:13:28,841 --> 00:13:29,642
overtreatment

266
00:13:29,842 --> 00:13:30,876
has happened more than once or twice.

267
00:13:31,477 --> 00:13:32,011
As director

268
00:13:32,011 --> 00:13:33,412
of Cardiology,

269
00:13:33,846 --> 00:13:35,347
I plan to request that the hospital learn from this case

270
00:13:36,348 --> 00:13:37,750
and conduct a full review

271
00:13:38,050 --> 00:13:39,185
of all historical cases.

272
00:13:43,155 --> 00:13:44,156
Have the two of you

273
00:13:45,024 --> 00:13:47,159
had some conflict lately?

274
00:13:47,593 --> 00:13:48,928
I have no personal grudge against him.

275
00:13:51,397 --> 00:13:52,798
But I really can't stand by anymore.

276
00:13:53,632 --> 00:13:54,400
We can't allow him

277
00:13:54,433 --> 00:13:55,534
to keep bullying patients like this.

278
00:13:59,872 --> 00:14:00,272
President,

279
00:14:01,373 --> 00:14:02,007
last time,

280
00:14:02,374 --> 00:14:03,409
about Director Sheng's artificial heart

281
00:14:03,442 --> 00:14:04,276
operation,

282
00:14:05,010 --> 00:14:06,245
I remember you mentioned it to me.

283
00:14:07,346 --> 00:14:07,846
Xiaofeng,

284
00:14:09,148 --> 00:14:10,282
I trust you.

285
00:14:10,983 --> 00:14:12,117
Do you trust me?

286
00:14:13,319 --> 00:14:14,253
That's why this time,

287
00:14:15,154 --> 00:14:16,722
I've hidden nothing from you.

288
00:14:20,326 --> 00:14:20,826
Xiaofeng,

289
00:14:23,195 --> 00:14:23,863
first of all,

290
00:14:24,630 --> 00:14:25,631
I'm very grateful

291
00:14:25,631 --> 00:14:26,532
for your trust in me.

292
00:14:27,933 --> 00:14:28,934
But this time is different.

293
00:14:30,369 --> 00:14:31,704
This is a real-name report.

294
00:14:32,671 --> 00:14:34,306
Once the committee starts

295
00:14:34,373 --> 00:14:35,374
an investigation procedure,

296
00:14:36,275 --> 00:14:37,076
it cannot stop

297
00:14:37,209 --> 00:14:38,444
until there is a conclusion.

298
00:14:39,345 --> 00:14:40,412
If in the end

299
00:14:41,280 --> 00:14:43,215
no problem is found with Director Sheng,

300
00:14:44,049 --> 00:14:44,750
do you know

301
00:14:46,151 --> 00:14:46,919
what kind of price

302
00:14:46,919 --> 00:14:47,987
you will have to pay?

303
00:14:48,854 --> 00:14:49,488
Demotion.

304
00:14:51,490 --> 00:14:52,091
Rank reduction.

305
00:14:53,926 --> 00:14:55,227
Sacrificing my career.

306
00:14:57,997 --> 00:14:58,764
I know all of that.

307
00:15:00,132 --> 00:15:00,666
President Wang,

308
00:15:02,601 --> 00:15:03,569
I'm prepared.

309
00:15:06,005 --> 00:15:07,673
The evaluation and appraisal committee?

310
00:15:08,507 --> 00:15:09,675
For You Xiaoli's case?

311
00:15:10,242 --> 00:15:11,043
Yes, Director Sheng.

312
00:15:11,644 --> 00:15:12,544
There are some matters

313
00:15:12,645 --> 00:15:13,712
we need to ask you about.

314
00:15:17,283 --> 00:15:17,750
Right now?

315
00:15:18,350 --> 00:15:18,651
Yes.

316
00:15:19,084 --> 00:15:20,119
The experts and leaders

317
00:15:20,152 --> 00:15:21,887
are waiting in the meeting room.

318
00:15:47,313 --> 00:15:48,914
You're going head-to-head with him like this?

319
00:15:51,583 --> 00:15:52,151
Why?

320
00:15:54,186 --> 00:15:55,788
For You Xiaoli and Linlang.

321
00:15:56,188 --> 00:15:56,956
For past patients

322
00:15:57,489 --> 00:15:58,557
and future patients too.

323
00:16:02,394 --> 00:16:03,395
But everyone knows

324
00:16:03,495 --> 00:16:05,030
you and Sheng Nian are rivals.

325
00:16:05,264 --> 00:16:06,598
Your relationship has never been good.

326
00:16:07,266 --> 00:16:08,867
Although the family raised the issue,

327
00:16:09,335 --> 00:16:10,336
you are the one initiating

328
00:16:10,336 --> 00:16:11,470
the internal hospital process.

329
00:16:11,804 --> 00:16:13,072
What will the leaders

330
00:16:13,305 --> 00:16:14,206
and colleagues think of you?

331
00:16:15,074 --> 00:16:16,442
Some people who don't know the truth

332
00:16:16,608 --> 00:16:17,443
may think

333
00:16:17,443 --> 00:16:18,711
you're using public means for private revenge.

334
00:16:21,947 --> 00:16:23,382
You and Sheng Nian finally

335
00:16:23,449 --> 00:16:24,650
stopped interfering with each other.

336
00:16:24,950 --> 00:16:26,385
There's no need to gamble with yourself.

337
00:16:27,152 --> 00:16:28,454
Instead of confronting him head-on,

338
00:16:28,787 --> 00:16:30,389
you might as well think of another way,

339
00:16:30,589 --> 00:16:31,690
use some tactics.

340
00:16:32,191 --> 00:16:33,158
Why don't you change the approach? No.

341
00:16:33,826 --> 00:16:35,127
This has to be done openly.

342
00:16:35,928 --> 00:16:36,662
If I'm going to bring him down,

343
00:16:36,662 --> 00:16:37,830
I'll do it openly and aboveboard.

344
00:16:38,364 --> 00:16:39,398
Only then will the leadership understand

345
00:16:39,431 --> 00:16:40,265
my determination.

346
00:16:40,933 --> 00:16:41,567
I know both of you

347
00:16:41,667 --> 00:16:42,568
think I'm being impulsive.

348
00:16:43,736 --> 00:16:44,603
But I've thought it through.

349
00:16:45,170 --> 00:16:46,405
Sheng Nian is a poisonous thorn

350
00:16:46,438 --> 00:16:47,406
in the Heart Center.

351
00:16:48,040 --> 00:16:48,774
It has to be pulled out.

352
00:16:49,308 --> 00:16:50,042
That's true.

353
00:16:50,642 --> 00:16:51,910
But if the evidence is insufficient,

354
00:16:52,544 --> 00:16:54,113
you could both end up hurt.

355
00:16:54,613 --> 00:16:55,147
Yes.

356
00:16:55,647 --> 00:16:56,849
If Sheng Nian really

357
00:16:56,949 --> 00:16:57,883
gets through this,

358
00:16:58,317 --> 00:16:59,985
he'll definitely strike back hard.

359
00:17:02,855 --> 00:17:04,022
Someone has to try.

360
00:17:08,394 --> 00:17:10,062
Have you told Lin Yi about this?

361
00:17:11,063 --> 00:17:11,830
I haven't told him.

362
00:17:12,431 --> 00:17:13,399
I don't want to put him in a difficult position.

363
00:17:15,601 --> 00:17:16,735
He'll find out sooner or later.

364
00:17:17,903 --> 00:17:19,171
So will Sheng Nian.

365
00:17:19,805 --> 00:17:20,773
There are no secrets in a hospital.

366
00:17:24,443 --> 00:17:26,045
I've prepared for the worst.

367
00:17:26,845 --> 00:17:28,347
I can accept any outcome.

368
00:17:29,815 --> 00:17:30,582
But I believe

369
00:17:31,350 --> 00:17:31,950
the investigation team

370
00:17:32,718 --> 00:17:33,585
will definitely make

371
00:17:33,685 --> 00:17:34,753
a fair judgment.

372
00:17:47,032 --> 00:17:48,233
They all signed

373
00:17:48,267 --> 00:17:49,368
informed consent forms for the surgery.

374
00:17:50,002 --> 00:17:51,236
The indication for valve replacement

375
00:17:51,236 --> 00:17:52,171
was slightly broad,

376
00:17:52,571 --> 00:17:53,372
but it's not a major issue.

377
00:17:53,906 --> 00:17:54,640
Don't worry too much.

378
00:17:55,274 --> 00:17:56,775
That patient's daughter is too difficult.

379
00:17:57,609 --> 00:17:59,077
If she keeps pushing

380
00:17:59,111 --> 00:18:00,112
for an explanation,

381
00:18:00,279 --> 00:18:01,346
and the competent authorities start investigating,

382
00:18:01,413 --> 00:18:02,147
or even launch

383
00:18:02,281 --> 00:18:03,415
a forensic appraisal,

384
00:18:04,116 --> 00:18:05,751
then that batch of near-expiry valves

385
00:18:06,151 --> 00:18:07,086
won't stay hidden.

386
00:18:12,558 --> 00:18:14,326
Near-expiry valves are still qualified products.

387
00:18:14,693 --> 00:18:15,561
They weren't expired.

388
00:18:17,262 --> 00:18:18,530
I shouldn't have softened

389
00:18:18,564 --> 00:18:19,431
and done you this favor.

390
00:18:21,467 --> 00:18:22,401
Now it's come to this.

391
00:18:23,135 --> 00:18:24,803
Everything will be dragged into the open.

392
00:18:25,204 --> 00:18:26,605
Just the overtreatment issue alone

393
00:18:26,638 --> 00:18:27,506
will be hard for us to get past.

394
00:18:28,307 --> 00:18:29,241
The original imaging,

395
00:18:29,508 --> 00:18:30,342
medical records and documents

396
00:18:30,609 --> 00:18:32,010
will all be scrutinized.

397
00:18:33,345 --> 00:18:33,679
Director,

398
00:18:34,513 --> 00:18:35,447
please calm down first.

399
00:18:36,048 --> 00:18:37,115
She's just a kid.

400
00:18:37,950 --> 00:18:38,951
I'll handle this.

401
00:18:39,685 --> 00:18:40,752
I won't let them

402
00:18:40,786 --> 00:18:41,553
come bother you again.

403
00:18:45,691 --> 00:18:46,291
How is it going?

404
00:18:47,125 --> 00:18:47,926
The infection is under control.

405
00:18:50,429 --> 00:18:51,763
It's been over a week.

406
00:18:51,997 --> 00:18:53,165
What she means is,

407
00:18:53,198 --> 00:18:53,599
once ECMO

408
00:18:53,599 --> 00:18:54,233
reaches two weeks,

409
00:18:54,266 --> 00:18:55,200
she'll give up.

410
00:18:56,635 --> 00:18:57,669
Next, we wait for a donor

411
00:18:57,836 --> 00:18:58,637
and see what fate has in store for her.

412
00:18:59,238 --> 00:19:00,172
President Wang came

413
00:19:00,172 --> 00:19:01,106
to see her this morning too.

414
00:19:01,707 --> 00:19:02,641
Once a patient is on ECMO,

415
00:19:02,674 --> 00:19:03,509
it's an emergency.

416
00:19:03,742 --> 00:19:05,410
He said he would also follow up closely.

417
00:19:08,046 --> 00:19:09,248
I hope she gets lucky.

418
00:19:27,065 --> 00:19:28,000
I'm already grateful

419
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:30,169
that you agreed to move visiting time

420
00:19:30,269 --> 00:19:31,303
to after school.

421
00:19:31,570 --> 00:19:32,638
And you're even taking care of my dinner.

422
00:19:33,005 --> 00:19:34,006
I'm really embarrassed.

423
00:19:34,072 --> 00:19:35,274
It's nothing.

424
00:19:36,074 --> 00:19:37,209
Adults taking care of children

425
00:19:37,743 --> 00:19:38,877
is only right.

426
00:19:39,011 --> 00:19:39,878
Here.

427
00:19:41,547 --> 00:19:41,914
Have some more soup.

428
00:19:42,614 --> 00:19:43,549
Thank you.

429
00:19:44,683 --> 00:19:45,450
What's wrong?

430
00:19:57,596 --> 00:19:58,197
I'm sorry.

431
00:20:01,133 --> 00:20:01,934
I should have listened to you.

432
00:20:02,768 --> 00:20:04,603
Then

433
00:20:05,971 --> 00:20:06,638
Mom wouldn't have ended up

434
00:20:07,306 --> 00:20:08,173
like this.

435
00:20:08,207 --> 00:20:09,107
It's not your fault.

436
00:20:11,944 --> 00:20:12,811
Right now, the urgent thing

437
00:20:13,345 --> 00:20:14,913
is to look forward.

438
00:20:15,013 --> 00:20:16,148
Active treatment matters most.

439
00:20:16,448 --> 00:20:17,849
Have some more.

440
00:20:21,186 --> 00:20:21,787
So, Dr. Fang,

441
00:20:24,690 --> 00:20:25,724
I don't care about any two-week limit.

442
00:20:26,992 --> 00:20:29,027
The money Mom left me

443
00:20:30,162 --> 00:20:31,263
was for necessary living expenses.

444
00:20:31,663 --> 00:20:33,332
But Mom is the most necessary,

445
00:20:34,132 --> 00:20:35,834
most essential thing in my life.

446
00:20:36,134 --> 00:20:37,569
I will never give up on her.

447
00:20:39,805 --> 00:20:41,039
Even if I have to spend

448
00:20:41,974 --> 00:20:42,808
the very last cent,

449
00:20:42,808 --> 00:20:43,709
and use the last bit of my strength,

450
00:20:44,343 --> 00:20:45,844
I'll hold on to the end.

451
00:20:46,211 --> 00:20:47,279
Then let's keep fighting together

452
00:20:48,647 --> 00:20:49,948
and help her hold on

453
00:20:50,682 --> 00:20:51,783
until the day a donor comes.

454
00:20:51,917 --> 00:20:53,485
At this critical point in the competition,

455
00:21:27,853 --> 00:21:28,954
you filed a real-name report against your rival.

456
00:21:30,389 --> 00:21:31,823
I really can't understand

457
00:21:33,291 --> 00:21:34,326
what you're after.

458
00:21:34,960 --> 00:21:35,694
You want a reputation

459
00:21:36,561 --> 00:21:37,763
for stopping at nothing to remove rivals?

460
00:21:37,929 --> 00:21:39,131
Who would dare entrust you with responsibility

461
00:21:40,032 --> 00:21:42,067
in the future?

462
00:21:43,335 --> 00:21:44,002
I'm not after anything.

463
00:21:44,770 --> 00:21:45,637
I just want justice

464
00:21:45,671 --> 00:21:46,672
for the patient.

465
00:21:47,572 --> 00:21:48,040
Come on.

466
00:21:49,708 --> 00:21:50,809
Stop putting on that lofty act

467
00:21:50,842 --> 00:21:51,677
and pretending to be noble.

468
00:21:52,911 --> 00:21:53,679
Have you forgotten

469
00:21:54,813 --> 00:21:55,847
how you treated

470
00:21:55,847 --> 00:21:56,715
your own mother before?

471
00:21:58,917 --> 00:22:00,252
In Dongjiang's medical circle,

472
00:22:01,319 --> 00:22:03,155
you're the number one wolf cub.

473
00:22:06,491 --> 00:22:07,559
Think whatever you want.

474
00:22:08,326 --> 00:22:09,795
If you believe you did nothing wrong,

475
00:22:10,762 --> 00:22:11,963
just cooperate with the investigation.

476
00:22:14,733 --> 00:22:16,168
If someone takes up a magnifying glass

477
00:22:16,635 --> 00:22:17,602
and checks carefully,

478
00:22:19,004 --> 00:22:20,272
who can guarantee

479
00:22:20,505 --> 00:22:21,440
they have no problems at all?

480
00:22:22,708 --> 00:22:24,209
Do you think your own hands are clean?

481
00:22:25,744 --> 00:22:27,312
A while ago, you led Cardiology

482
00:22:27,346 --> 00:22:28,146
in pushing that

483
00:22:28,146 --> 00:22:29,281
one-stop atrial fibrillation treatment.

484
00:22:30,649 --> 00:22:31,917
Weren't you just one step away too?

485
00:22:33,385 --> 00:22:34,720
That one step is exactly the point.

486
00:22:36,388 --> 00:22:37,322
You took it.

487
00:22:38,156 --> 00:22:38,724
I didn't.

488
00:22:42,227 --> 00:22:43,595
Those who achieve great things

489
00:22:44,529 --> 00:22:45,630
don't fuss over minor details.

490
00:22:46,064 --> 00:22:47,599
If technology is to advance

491
00:22:48,166 --> 00:22:49,267
and departments are to develop,

492
00:22:49,468 --> 00:22:50,936
you have to take bigger steps.

493
00:22:51,069 --> 00:22:52,037
When everyone is stepping forward,

494
00:22:52,170 --> 00:22:53,438
no one cares about the ants underfoot.

495
00:22:53,572 --> 00:22:54,840
Patients are not ants.

496
00:22:55,173 --> 00:22:56,475
They are people.

497
00:22:56,908 --> 00:22:58,009
Someone's family.

498
00:22:58,510 --> 00:22:59,644
They are not sacrifices

499
00:22:59,678 --> 00:23:00,479
on your path upward.

500
00:23:09,788 --> 00:23:10,756
I really don't know

501
00:23:12,891 --> 00:23:14,426
whether to call you an idealist

502
00:23:15,494 --> 00:23:16,194
or naive.

503
00:23:17,896 --> 00:23:18,964
Why bother?

504
00:23:20,232 --> 00:23:21,933
Wouldn't it be better to go with the flow?

505
00:23:23,668 --> 00:23:24,603
All along,

506
00:23:25,303 --> 00:23:26,004
I admit

507
00:23:27,105 --> 00:23:28,473
I never took you seriously.

508
00:23:29,875 --> 00:23:31,410
A wet-behind-the-ears kid

509
00:23:31,810 --> 00:23:32,844
who was born into the right family,

510
00:23:33,078 --> 00:23:33,945
with his mother paving the way.

511
00:23:34,746 --> 00:23:35,680
But now it seems

512
00:23:36,915 --> 00:23:39,151
your face is clearly full of ambition,

513
00:23:39,317 --> 00:23:40,919
yet you insist on holding on to that bit of integrity.

514
00:23:43,288 --> 00:23:43,889
Aren't you tired?

515
00:23:47,993 --> 00:23:48,927
That one bit

516
00:23:50,395 --> 00:23:51,196
is what I don't want to lose.

517
00:23:53,932 --> 00:23:55,200
That's why I hate you.

518
00:23:57,869 --> 00:23:58,670
Same to you.

519
00:23:59,504 --> 00:24:00,238
Take care of yourself.

520
00:24:23,128 --> 00:24:23,562
Hello?

521
00:24:23,895 --> 00:24:24,362
Sheng Nian,

522
00:24:24,796 --> 00:24:25,764
come to my office.

523
00:24:26,231 --> 00:24:26,598
Okay.

524
00:24:35,307 --> 00:24:35,807
President.

525
00:24:38,076 --> 00:24:38,844
You're Sheng Nian, right?

526
00:24:40,412 --> 00:24:40,846
That's me.

527
00:24:43,648 --> 00:24:44,749
We are staff members from the Dongjiang Municipal

528
00:24:44,850 --> 00:24:46,184
Discipline Inspection and Supervision Commission.

529
00:24:47,118 --> 00:24:47,853
We need you

530
00:24:47,919 --> 00:24:48,920
to assist with an investigation.

531
00:24:49,354 --> 00:24:50,088
Please cooperate.

532
00:24:54,626 --> 00:24:55,894
You Xiaoli's family member

533
00:24:55,994 --> 00:24:57,128
and designated guardian

534
00:24:57,329 --> 00:24:58,163
filed a real-name report

535
00:24:58,196 --> 00:24:59,598
accusing you and a device supplier

536
00:24:59,631 --> 00:25:00,532
of collusion.

537
00:25:01,166 --> 00:25:02,634
Qin Xiong used your name

538
00:25:02,734 --> 00:25:04,202
to negotiate with the family

539
00:25:04,369 --> 00:25:05,504
and transferred 200,000 yuan to them.

540
00:25:05,871 --> 00:25:07,005
In my name?

541
00:25:08,073 --> 00:25:09,040
What kind of joke is that?

542
00:25:09,574 --> 00:25:10,509
I know nothing

543
00:25:10,542 --> 00:25:11,309
about this.

544
00:25:12,043 --> 00:25:13,311
And I know nothing about any 200,000 yuan.

545
00:25:14,880 --> 00:25:15,614
Where is Sheng Nian?

546
00:25:16,281 --> 00:25:17,649
Is Director Sheng really not coming?

547
00:25:22,854 --> 00:25:23,855
Who comes doesn't matter.

548
00:25:25,190 --> 00:25:26,525
What matters is that I can help you.

549
00:25:27,092 --> 00:25:27,926
I don't even know you.

550
00:25:28,026 --> 00:25:28,994
Why should I trust you?

551
00:25:29,528 --> 00:25:30,795
Tell Sheng Nian to come talk to me.

552
00:25:31,329 --> 00:25:32,964
Director Sheng is a very senior director.

553
00:25:33,331 --> 00:25:34,533
He's busy every day.

554
00:25:35,233 --> 00:25:36,034
He can't possibly handle

555
00:25:36,167 --> 00:25:37,302
everything personally.

556
00:25:38,036 --> 00:25:39,237
He authorized me to come.

557
00:25:39,971 --> 00:25:40,472
Don't worry.

558
00:25:41,473 --> 00:25:43,041
We are very sincere.

559
00:25:43,675 --> 00:25:44,442
The urgent priority

560
00:25:44,476 --> 00:25:45,844
is treating your mother.

561
00:25:47,512 --> 00:25:48,547
Take this 200,000 yuan.

562
00:25:49,814 --> 00:25:50,548
If it's not enough,

563
00:25:50,949 --> 00:25:52,450
we'll think of other ways later.

564
00:25:55,086 --> 00:25:55,587
Go on, take it.

565
00:25:57,489 --> 00:25:59,624
How could I possibly authorize him?

566
00:26:01,326 --> 00:26:02,160
That Qin Xiong

567
00:26:02,160 --> 00:26:03,762
is talking complete nonsense.

568
00:26:06,798 --> 00:26:08,333
Here, take a good look.

569
00:26:09,067 --> 00:26:11,036
This is You Xiaoli's operative record.

570
00:26:11,836 --> 00:26:13,505
Aside from the VSD repair,

571
00:26:13,905 --> 00:26:14,839
during the surgery,

572
00:26:15,173 --> 00:26:17,075
you also replaced her aortic valve.

573
00:26:19,044 --> 00:26:21,479
What was the consideration behind that?

574
00:26:24,249 --> 00:26:25,850
Look at what's written here.

575
00:26:26,718 --> 00:26:28,386
Suspected overtreatment.

576
00:26:29,587 --> 00:26:31,623
The surgical indication

577
00:26:31,957 --> 00:26:32,924
can still be debated.

578
00:26:33,491 --> 00:26:34,359
But if it's really like

579
00:26:34,392 --> 00:26:35,026
what is written above,

580
00:26:35,393 --> 00:26:37,495
and there was a financial relationship

581
00:26:37,596 --> 00:26:38,797
with the supplier,

582
00:26:39,197 --> 00:26:39,931
then this becomes troublesome.

583
00:26:40,966 --> 00:26:41,833
This doesn't seem like

584
00:26:41,833 --> 00:26:42,968
Director Sheng's style.

585
00:26:43,435 --> 00:26:43,935
Why would he

586
00:26:43,969 --> 00:26:45,103
ask a device vendor to step in

587
00:26:45,170 --> 00:26:46,171
to settle this matter,

588
00:26:46,371 --> 00:26:47,973
and let someone catch him red-handed?

589
00:26:49,607 --> 00:26:50,508
I heard

590
00:26:50,976 --> 00:26:52,711
that the family recorded it at the time.

591
00:26:52,844 --> 00:26:53,878
What's the situation now?

592
00:26:55,080 --> 00:26:56,414
Director Sheng is still under investigation.

593
00:26:56,815 --> 00:26:58,483
If he can come back

594
00:26:58,717 --> 00:27:00,518
within twelve hours,

595
00:27:00,585 --> 00:27:01,286
or twenty-four hours at most,

596
00:27:01,386 --> 00:27:02,454
then I guess

597
00:27:02,854 --> 00:27:03,722
he's passed this hurdle.

598
00:27:04,522 --> 00:27:05,690
If he still doesn't come back,

599
00:27:06,191 --> 00:27:06,791
then

600
00:27:07,225 --> 00:27:08,026
it's probably not good.

601
00:27:08,760 --> 00:27:09,995
Director Sheng has called for rounds.

602
00:27:10,161 --> 00:27:11,496
He's already waiting by the nurses' station.

603
00:27:12,030 --> 00:27:12,597
Who?

604
00:27:12,797 --> 00:27:13,398
Director Sheng.

605
00:27:18,003 --> 00:27:18,403
Dong.

606
00:27:20,271 --> 00:27:20,805
Thanks, bro.

607
00:28:00,512 --> 00:28:01,413
How could Sheng Nian

608
00:28:01,413 --> 00:28:02,547
get through it just like that?

609
00:28:04,149 --> 00:28:04,949
If even the discipline commission

610
00:28:04,949 --> 00:28:06,351
couldn't find anything,

611
00:28:06,684 --> 00:28:08,353
then the evidence must not be sufficient.

612
00:28:09,521 --> 00:28:10,255
I guess the hospital's

613
00:28:10,288 --> 00:28:11,489
internal evaluation committee

614
00:28:11,823 --> 00:28:12,991
won't make much of a splash either.

615
00:28:14,626 --> 00:28:15,827
Old Qin was taken away too.

616
00:28:16,194 --> 00:28:17,762
He still hasn't been sent back.

617
00:28:18,830 --> 00:28:19,798
Qin Xiong's situation

618
00:28:20,432 --> 00:28:21,933
is probably more complicated than Sheng Nian's.

619
00:28:24,369 --> 00:28:25,170
But I still believe

620
00:28:25,170 --> 00:28:26,271
what Linlang said is true.

621
00:28:27,305 --> 00:28:28,273
It's just that without evidence,

622
00:28:28,373 --> 00:28:29,207
it's hard to determine the nature of it.

623
00:28:31,009 --> 00:28:32,544
But if that's the case,

624
00:28:33,411 --> 00:28:34,846
you were the one who knocked over

625
00:28:34,879 --> 00:28:35,847
the first domino.

626
00:28:37,048 --> 00:28:37,882
If Sheng Nian

627
00:28:38,216 --> 00:28:39,384
really gets through this,

628
00:28:39,384 --> 00:28:40,952
your days at the hospital will be very difficult.

629
00:28:43,288 --> 00:28:44,789
We'll face whatever comes.

630
00:28:46,224 --> 00:28:46,725
What about you?

631
00:28:47,192 --> 00:28:48,159
With Qin Xiong in trouble,

632
00:28:48,393 --> 00:28:49,094
the whole region

633
00:28:49,127 --> 00:28:50,695
will probably be reshuffled, right?

634
00:28:52,330 --> 00:28:53,398
President Qin still hasn't come back?

635
00:28:53,765 --> 00:28:54,766
No, Sister Ouyang.

636
00:28:55,233 --> 00:28:56,801
It's been a whole day and night.

637
00:28:58,203 --> 00:29:00,004
They came straight in and took him away.

638
00:29:00,472 --> 00:29:01,306
They also took the financial statements

639
00:29:01,406 --> 00:29:02,173
and everything else.

640
00:29:02,707 --> 00:29:03,608
I think this time,

641
00:29:03,975 --> 00:29:04,542
it's serious.

642
00:29:23,128 --> 00:29:23,928
Are you in a hurry to get home?

643
00:29:25,029 --> 00:29:25,964
No, I'm not.

644
00:29:26,464 --> 00:29:27,332
This is milk tea

645
00:29:27,332 --> 00:29:28,366
I ordered specially for you.

646
00:29:29,267 --> 00:29:30,668
Your usual standard: thirty percent sugar.

647
00:29:30,769 --> 00:29:31,436
Thank you, boss.

648
00:29:31,970 --> 00:29:33,104
Consider it me asking Senlin

649
00:29:33,171 --> 00:29:34,038
to give you some time off.

650
00:29:35,473 --> 00:29:36,374
It's rare to have time.

651
00:29:37,108 --> 00:29:37,976
Stay and chat with me.

652
00:29:39,811 --> 00:29:40,512
Boss, why are you

653
00:29:40,612 --> 00:29:41,679
in the mood for this today?

654
00:29:42,680 --> 00:29:45,316
You've been with the company for more than a year, right?

655
00:29:46,518 --> 00:29:47,685
I came early last year.

656
00:29:52,991 --> 00:29:54,025
When you first arrived,

657
00:29:54,626 --> 00:29:55,827
I really didn't expect

658
00:29:56,127 --> 00:29:58,029
you to become top seller in one year.

659
00:30:01,866 --> 00:30:03,535
If the other sales reps

660
00:30:03,768 --> 00:30:05,036
were all talent like you,

661
00:30:06,571 --> 00:30:07,438
then the company

662
00:30:08,039 --> 00:30:08,673
certainly wouldn't be

663
00:30:08,706 --> 00:30:09,774
in its current state.

664
00:30:10,308 --> 00:30:11,242
Listen to you.

665
00:30:11,476 --> 00:30:12,210
Isn't our company doing

666
00:30:12,277 --> 00:30:13,344
pretty well right now?

667
00:30:15,146 --> 00:30:16,548
At first, I actually thought

668
00:30:17,148 --> 00:30:18,116
whether you're a doctor

669
00:30:18,216 --> 00:30:19,284
or a sales rep,

670
00:30:19,784 --> 00:30:21,920
you earn money through

671
00:30:21,986 --> 00:30:22,921
technology and service.

672
00:30:23,354 --> 00:30:24,823
You can absolutely earn respectable money.

673
00:30:27,225 --> 00:30:28,226
Respectable money.

674
00:30:29,794 --> 00:30:30,895
In our line of work,

675
00:30:31,029 --> 00:30:32,430
it isn't easy

676
00:30:33,031 --> 00:30:33,998
to stay respectable forever.

677
00:30:34,933 --> 00:30:36,067
In the larger environment,

678
00:30:37,335 --> 00:30:38,169
sometimes you really

679
00:30:40,438 --> 00:30:41,239
can't help yourself.

680
00:30:42,207 --> 00:30:43,608
I refuse to believe that.

681
00:30:43,875 --> 00:30:44,709
I can't control others,

682
00:30:45,009 --> 00:30:46,244
but I can discipline myself.

683
00:30:46,744 --> 00:30:47,846
I'll just walk my own path.

684
00:30:48,213 --> 00:30:50,048
It may indeed be harder,

685
00:30:50,515 --> 00:30:51,349
but at least

686
00:30:51,516 --> 00:30:52,884
I can sleep at night.

687
00:30:57,755 --> 00:30:58,790
That drive of yours

688
00:30:59,357 --> 00:31:00,124
is truly rare.

689
00:31:05,563 --> 00:31:07,332
Who doesn't have some pride?

690
00:31:09,467 --> 00:31:10,668
I've been in this industry for thirty years.

691
00:31:11,469 --> 00:31:12,303
At the beginning,

692
00:31:12,437 --> 00:31:13,271
I worked for manufacturers.

693
00:31:14,706 --> 00:31:15,807
Being a pharmaceutical and device representative

694
00:31:15,974 --> 00:31:17,842
was a very respectable profession.

695
00:31:19,510 --> 00:31:20,745
Every time we went to the hospital for meetings,

696
00:31:21,512 --> 00:31:22,513
department directors would come

697
00:31:22,714 --> 00:31:23,948
downstairs to greet us.

698
00:31:24,949 --> 00:31:26,050
Because we represented

699
00:31:26,150 --> 00:31:27,552
advanced professional technology.

700
00:31:29,954 --> 00:31:30,922
We were highly respected.

701
00:31:33,992 --> 00:31:35,627
When did that change?

702
00:31:39,430 --> 00:31:40,365
You're right.

703
00:31:41,866 --> 00:31:43,234
The environment isn't an excuse.

704
00:31:45,303 --> 00:31:47,238
The key lies in yourself.

705
00:31:50,041 --> 00:31:50,575
Drink your milk tea.

706
00:31:57,448 --> 00:31:57,949
Ouyang.

707
00:31:59,851 --> 00:32:01,953
About changing your region, I wronged you.

708
00:32:02,754 --> 00:32:03,454
Don't resent me.

709
00:32:04,355 --> 00:32:05,390
Please don't say that.

710
00:32:06,724 --> 00:32:07,558
Actually,

711
00:32:09,694 --> 00:32:10,795
I still need to thank you.

712
00:32:12,563 --> 00:32:13,331
Thank you

713
00:32:13,731 --> 00:32:15,133
for helping me find funding for Doudou.

714
00:32:15,433 --> 00:32:16,134
Doudou's mom said

715
00:32:16,167 --> 00:32:17,402
that after he recovers,

716
00:32:17,835 --> 00:32:19,103
she wants to come thank you in person.

717
00:32:26,210 --> 00:32:27,145
As long as the child is safe.

718
00:32:29,113 --> 00:32:30,915
At least I did one good thing.

719
00:32:34,285 --> 00:32:35,253
It's late. Go home.

720
00:32:40,692 --> 00:32:41,893
That money tree

721
00:32:43,394 --> 00:32:44,195
will be yours later.

722
00:32:45,196 --> 00:32:46,030
I wouldn't dare.

723
00:32:46,264 --> 00:32:47,632
That's your money tree.

724
00:32:50,068 --> 00:32:50,601
Go on.

725
00:33:04,282 --> 00:33:08,052
Regarding suspected disciplinary and legal violations...

726
00:33:08,453 --> 00:33:09,253
Sheng Nian.

727
00:33:09,954 --> 00:33:10,855
Director Sheng from Cardiac Surgery.

728
00:33:10,855 --> 00:33:11,889
Overseas account.

729
00:33:13,791 --> 00:33:14,559
So many zeros.

730
00:33:15,793 --> 00:33:17,795
Ones, tens, hundreds, thousands,

731
00:33:17,829 --> 00:33:18,763
ten thousands, hundred thousands, millions...

732
00:33:19,597 --> 00:33:20,398
My goodness.

733
00:33:20,598 --> 00:33:21,199
So much money.

734
00:33:21,232 --> 00:33:22,533
How could he ever spend it all?

735
00:33:22,834 --> 00:33:24,168
These people are way too bold.

736
00:33:24,235 --> 00:33:25,002
They thought that overseas

737
00:33:25,002 --> 00:33:25,803
meant it couldn't be traced.

738
00:33:25,903 --> 00:33:26,504
What's going on?

739
00:33:26,671 --> 00:33:27,305
Come on, make way, everyone.

740
00:33:27,372 --> 00:33:27,705
Make way.

741
00:33:27,772 --> 00:33:28,473
Disperse, disperse.

742
00:33:28,473 --> 00:33:28,773
Make way.

743
00:33:28,773 --> 00:33:29,307
There's nothing to see.

744
00:33:29,407 --> 00:33:29,874
Everyone disperse.

745
00:33:30,008 --> 00:33:30,708
Nothing to see here.

746
00:33:30,775 --> 00:33:31,409
Disperse. Disperse.

747
00:33:57,635 --> 00:33:58,069
Hello?

748
00:34:00,071 --> 00:34:00,671
Director Sheng.

749
00:34:03,207 --> 00:34:04,275
Qin Xiong is inside.

750
00:34:06,110 --> 00:34:07,078
He confessed everything.

751
00:35:13,344 --> 00:35:13,811
Hello?

752
00:35:14,212 --> 00:35:14,745
Son.

753
00:35:15,446 --> 00:35:15,947
Hello?

754
00:35:16,614 --> 00:35:17,048
Mom.

755
00:35:18,282 --> 00:35:19,117
Have you had breakfast?

756
00:35:20,117 --> 00:35:20,551
Yes.

757
00:35:21,986 --> 00:35:22,453
Where's Dad?

758
00:35:23,287 --> 00:35:24,322
He went grocery shopping.

759
00:35:26,023 --> 00:35:27,225
Why is it so noisy over there?

760
00:35:27,825 --> 00:35:28,526
Are you outside?

761
00:35:29,160 --> 00:35:31,195
I'm exercising here in the park.

762
00:35:32,964 --> 00:35:34,265
It's been cold again these two days.

763
00:35:35,266 --> 00:35:36,334
Go home right after exercising.

764
00:35:36,367 --> 00:35:37,068
Don't catch a cold.

765
00:35:37,635 --> 00:35:39,403
You're the one who told me to exercise,

766
00:35:39,637 --> 00:35:41,272
and now you're the one telling me to go home.

767
00:35:42,507 --> 00:35:43,374
Why are you calling

768
00:35:43,374 --> 00:35:44,275
so early in the morning?

769
00:35:44,308 --> 00:35:45,209
Is something wrong?

770
00:35:46,110 --> 00:35:47,512
When I'm busy and don't call,

771
00:35:47,612 --> 00:35:48,479
you nag me.

772
00:35:49,247 --> 00:35:50,348
Now that I'm calling,

773
00:35:50,448 --> 00:35:51,282
you nag me too.

774
00:35:52,850 --> 00:35:54,185
It's still better to call more often.

775
00:35:55,553 --> 00:35:56,721
You're not busy today, are you?

776
00:35:56,988 --> 00:35:58,322
Come home for dinner tonight.

777
00:35:58,623 --> 00:36:01,192
I'll cook hairtail and stew some ribs.

778
00:36:01,626 --> 00:36:02,493
We still haven't finished

779
00:36:02,527 --> 00:36:03,594
the ribs you bought.

780
00:36:04,128 --> 00:36:06,197
Your dad keeps saying we should wait for you to come back and eat them.

781
00:36:06,364 --> 00:36:06,797
All right.

782
00:36:07,465 --> 00:36:08,232
Go exercise.

783
00:36:08,866 --> 00:36:09,567
Get some proper rest.

784
00:36:09,967 --> 00:36:10,635
Take care of yourself.

785
00:36:13,504 --> 00:36:14,872
So are you coming back for dinner?

786
00:36:38,563 --> 00:36:38,963
Hello?

787
00:36:40,197 --> 00:36:41,399
Sheng Nian isn't in his office.

788
00:36:42,266 --> 00:36:43,734
Keep watch by the main gate.

789
00:36:44,569 --> 00:36:45,636
I'll see if I can arrange another team

790
00:36:45,770 --> 00:36:46,637
to wait at his home.

791
00:36:47,605 --> 00:36:47,972
Yes.

792
00:36:48,706 --> 00:36:49,040
Okay.

793
00:36:49,574 --> 00:36:50,208
Keep me updated.

794
00:36:50,808 --> 00:36:51,542
We must find him.

795
00:37:33,918 --> 00:37:34,352
Director Sheng.

796
00:37:34,652 --> 00:37:35,319
Sorry.

797
00:37:35,553 --> 00:37:36,287
This gate is normally

798
00:37:36,320 --> 00:37:37,188
entrance only.

799
00:37:37,355 --> 00:37:38,589
Why don't you use the main entrance?

800
00:37:39,557 --> 00:37:40,524
I'm rushing to surgery.

801
00:37:40,958 --> 00:37:42,393
If someone dies because of the delay, will you take responsibility?

802
00:37:43,094 --> 00:37:43,561
Open the gate.

803
00:37:45,129 --> 00:37:45,496
All right.

804
00:37:45,763 --> 00:37:47,031
Then please don't tell my supervisor.

805
00:38:11,922 --> 00:38:12,723
Airway pressure is rising.

806
00:38:12,757 --> 00:38:13,557
Tidal volume is dropping.

807
00:38:14,225 --> 00:38:15,226
Oxygen saturation is only eighty.

808
00:38:19,130 --> 00:38:20,131
There's blood in the endotracheal tube.

809
00:38:20,197 --> 00:38:20,665
Suction.

810
00:38:20,865 --> 00:38:21,732
Prepare the bronchoscope.

811
00:38:21,766 --> 00:38:22,066
Okay.

812
00:38:23,134 --> 00:38:23,934
Run a full coagulation panel.

813
00:38:24,001 --> 00:38:24,568
Bedside ultrasound.

814
00:38:24,635 --> 00:38:24,969
Okay.

815
00:38:39,984 --> 00:38:40,918
You told me before

816
00:38:42,920 --> 00:38:44,388
that if it didn't come from your own mouth,

817
00:38:45,756 --> 00:38:46,590
I shouldn't believe it.

818
00:38:52,763 --> 00:38:53,564
Is this true?

819
00:39:01,706 --> 00:39:02,907
Whether it's true or false,

820
00:39:03,674 --> 00:39:04,308
does it matter?

821
00:39:07,712 --> 00:39:08,312
I really don't know

822
00:39:08,312 --> 00:39:09,480
whether I should envy you.

823
00:39:11,248 --> 00:39:12,683
You're almost forty,

824
00:39:14,518 --> 00:39:15,720
yet you still live in a vacuum.

825
00:39:21,992 --> 00:39:22,693
Are your illusions shattered?

826
00:39:26,931 --> 00:39:28,065
If this world

827
00:39:28,733 --> 00:39:30,668
could be measured only by truth, falsehood, right and wrong,

828
00:39:33,170 --> 00:39:34,205
then it would be too simple.

829
00:39:35,005 --> 00:39:36,240
Not complicated at all.

830
00:39:39,543 --> 00:39:40,511
Money, power...

831
00:39:40,544 --> 00:39:41,412
What do these things

832
00:39:41,412 --> 00:39:42,346
have to do with being a doctor?

833
00:39:43,681 --> 00:39:45,282
I took the college entrance exam at sixteen.

834
00:39:48,385 --> 00:39:49,387
I chose medical school.

835
00:39:49,954 --> 00:39:51,389
I completed my bachelor's, master's, and doctorate,

836
00:39:52,089 --> 00:39:53,290
then went abroad for postdoctoral training

837
00:39:53,591 --> 00:39:54,492
and earned a postdoc.

838
00:39:55,292 --> 00:39:57,361
I suppose I was one of the favored few,

839
00:39:58,162 --> 00:39:59,063
achieving success at a young age.

840
00:40:00,197 --> 00:40:00,998
My path

841
00:40:02,533 --> 00:40:03,734
was smooth all the way.

842
00:40:05,636 --> 00:40:06,637
Since you were so outstanding,

843
00:40:06,704 --> 00:40:07,505
you should have become

844
00:40:07,638 --> 00:40:08,439
an even better doctor.

845
00:40:08,973 --> 00:40:10,174
Why choose this path?

846
00:40:11,008 --> 00:40:11,675
At the beginning,

847
00:40:11,909 --> 00:40:13,110
everyone has ideals

848
00:40:13,144 --> 00:40:13,844
and passion.

849
00:40:18,416 --> 00:40:19,984
Once certain lines are crossed,

850
00:40:22,987 --> 00:40:24,288
one wrong step

851
00:40:25,189 --> 00:40:25,956
leads to every step going wrong.

852
00:40:28,793 --> 00:40:29,527
There's no turning back.

853
00:40:34,799 --> 00:40:35,533
Of course there is.

854
00:40:37,968 --> 00:40:38,869
If you turn yourself in now,

855
00:40:39,370 --> 00:40:40,171
that is turning back.

856
00:40:51,649 --> 00:40:52,249
And then?

857
00:40:55,319 --> 00:40:57,154
Spend the second half of my life in prison?

858
00:40:57,721 --> 00:40:59,123
Locked up for ten or twenty years?

859
00:41:02,426 --> 00:41:03,494
But you did something wrong.

860
00:41:03,561 --> 00:41:05,296
If you do wrong, you should take responsibility.

861
00:41:11,969 --> 00:41:13,103
I know.

862
00:41:14,805 --> 00:41:15,506
Okay.

863
00:41:15,606 --> 00:41:17,508
Don't worry, Teacher Sanshui.

864
00:41:18,609 --> 00:41:20,544
I can eat, drink, and sleep.

865
00:41:22,146 --> 00:41:23,047
Don't...

866
00:41:23,280 --> 00:41:24,849
Stop talking to me like I'm a child,

867
00:41:24,849 --> 00:41:25,516
will you?

868
00:41:28,252 --> 00:41:28,953
Who is that?

869
00:41:29,286 --> 00:41:30,554
Honking so loudly.

870
00:41:30,955 --> 00:41:31,856
So rude.

871
00:41:32,556 --> 00:41:33,290
It's fine, driver.

872
00:41:33,390 --> 00:41:34,792
Maybe something happened.

873
